label.value: positive regulation of neural retina development

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of neural retina development, the progression of the neural retina over time from its initial formation to the mature structure. The neural retina is the part of the retina that contains neurons and photoreceptor cells.

label.value: negative regulation of neural retina development

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of neural retina development, the progression of the neural retina over time from its initial formation to the mature structure. The neural retina is the part of the retina that contains neurons and photoreceptor cells.

label.value: chaperone-mediated protein folding

value.value: The process of inhibiting aggregation and assisting in the covalent and noncovalent assembly of single chain polypeptides or multisubunit complexes into the correct tertiary structure that is dependent on interaction with a chaperone.

label.value: positive regulation of prostaglandin secretion involved in immune response

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of a prostaglandin from a cell and contributes to the immune response.

label.value: left horn of sinus venosus development

value.value: The progression of the left horn of the sinus venosus from its initial formation to the mature structure.

label.value: right horn of sinus venosus development

value.value: The progression of the right horn of the sinus venosus from its formation to the mature structure.

label.value: positive regulation of myeloid leukocyte cytokine production involved in immune response

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the production of a cytokine that contributes to the immune response.

label.value: myeloid leukocyte cytokine production

value.value: Any process that contributes to cytokine production by a myeloid cell.

definition.value: Note that this term is in the subset of terms that should not be used for direct gene product annotation. Instead, select one of the 'regulation' children terms.

label.value: regulation of protein refolding

value.value: Any process that regulates the rate, frequency, or extent of protein refolding. Protein refolding is the process carried out by a cell that restores the biological activity of an unfolded or misfolded protein, using helper proteins such as chaperones.

label.value: negative regulation of protein refolding

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of protein refolding. Protein refolding is the process carried out by a cell that restores the biological activity of an unfolded or misfolded protein, using helper proteins such as chaperones.

label.value: regulation of phospholipid translocation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the translocation, or flipping, of phospholipid molecules from one monolayer of a membrane bilayer to the opposite monolayer.

label.value: positive regulation of phospholipid translocation

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the translocation, or flipping, of phospholipid molecules from one monolayer of a membrane bilayer to the opposite monolayer.

label.value: negative regulation of phospholipid translocation

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the translocation, or flipping, of phospholipid molecules from one monolayer of a membrane bilayer to the opposite monolayer.

label.value: regulation of turning behavior involved in mating

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of turning behavior involved in mating. Turning behavior is the sharp ventral turn performed by the male as he approaches either the hermaphrodite head or tail, whilst trying to locate his partner's vulva. Turning occurs via a sharp ventral coil of the male's tail.

label.value: positive regulation of turning behavior involved in mating

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of turning behavior involved in mating. Turning behavior is the sharp ventral turn performed by the male as he approaches either the hermaphrodite head or tail, whilst trying to locate his partner's vulva. Turning occurs via a sharp ventral coil of the male's tail.

label.value: negative regulation of turning behavior involved in mating

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of turning behavior involved in mating. Turning behavior is the sharp ventral turn performed by the male as he approaches either the hermaphrodite head or tail, whilst trying to locate his partner's vulva. Turning occurs via a sharp ventral coil of the male's tail.

label.value: regulation of protein tyrosine kinase activity

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of protein tyrosine kinase activity.

label.value: positive regulation of protein tyrosine kinase activity

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of protein tyrosine kinase activity.

label.value: negative regulation of protein tyrosine kinase activity

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of protein tyrosine kinase activity.

label.value: lung neuroendocrine cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuroendocrine cell of the lung epithelium.

label.value: neuroendocrine cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features of a neuroendocrine cell. A neuroendocrine cell is a cell that receives input form a neuron which controls the secretion of an endocrine substance.

label.value: stomach neuroendocrine cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuroendocrine cell of the stomach epithelium.

label.value: carotid body glomus cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features of a glomus cell of the carotid body. The carotid body is a specialized chemosensory organ that helps respond to hypoxia.

label.value: adrenal chromaffin cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features of an adrenal chromaffin cell. An adrenal chromaffin cell is a neuroendocrine cell that stores epinephrine secretory vesicles.

label.value: regulation of stomach neuroendocrine cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the differentiation of a neuroendocrine cell in the stomach.

label.value: negative regulation of stomach neuroendocrine cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of the differentiation of a neuroendocrine cell in the stomach.

label.value: seminal vesicle development

value.value: The progression of the seminal vesicle over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The seminal vesicle is a gland that contributes to the production of semen.

label.value: seminal vesicle epithelium development

value.value: The progression of the seminal vesicle epithelium over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label.value: dense core granule organization

value.value: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a dense core granule. A dense core granule is a secretory organelle found in endocrine cells.

label.value: dense core granule biogenesis

value.value: A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of a dense core granule. Includes biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, and those macromolecular modifications that are involved in synthesis or assembly of the dense core granule.

label.value: epithelial-mesenchymal cell signaling involved in lung development

value.value: Any process that results in the transfer of information from an epithelial cell to a mesenchymal cell and contributes to the progression of the lung over time from its initial formation to the mature organ.

label.value: negative regulation of bud outgrowth involved in lung branching

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of bud outgrowth involved in lung branching.

label.value: pancreas morphogenesis

value.value: Morphogenesis of the pancreas. Morphogenesis is the process in which anatomical structures are generated and organized.

label.value: branching involved in pancreas morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the branches of the pancreas are generated and organized.

label.value: lung proximal/distal axis specification

value.value: The establishment, maintenance and elaboration of the proximal/distal axis of the lung. The proximal/distal axis of the lung is defined by a line that runs from the trachea to the alveoli.

label.value: ductus venosus closure

value.value: The morphogenesis process in which the ductus venosus changes to no longer permit blood flow after birth.

label.value: negative regulation of heart growth

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate or extent of heart growth. Heart growth is the increase in size or mass of the heart.

label.value: regulation of positive chemotaxis to cAMP

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of directed movement of a motile cell or organism up a concentration gradient of 3',5'-cAMP.

label.value: regulation of positive chemotaxis to cAMP by chlorinated alkylphenone

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of directed movement of a motile cell or organism up a concentration gradient of 3',5'-cAMP by the action of a chlorinated alkylphenone. An alkylphenone is an aromatic polyketide with methyl and chlorine substitutions.

label.value: regulation of positive chemotaxis to cAMP by DIF-1

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of directed movement of a motile cell or organism up a concentration gradient of 3',5'-cAMP by the action of DIF-1. DIF-1 is a chlorinated alkylphenone.

label.value: regulation of positive chemotaxis to cAMP by DIF-2

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of directed movement of a motile cell or organism up a concentration gradient of 3',5'-cAMP by the action of DIF-2. DIF-2 is a chlorinated alkylphenone.

label.value: positive regulation of positive chemotaxis to cAMP

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of directed movement of a motile cell or organism up a concentration gradient of 3',5'-cAMP.

label.value: negative regulation of positive chemotaxis to cAMP

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of directed movement of a motile cell or organism up a concentration gradient of 3',5'-cAMP.

label.value: positive regulation of positive chemotaxis to cAMP by chlorinated alkylphenone

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of directed movement of a motile cell or organism up a concentration gradient of 3',5'-cAMP by the action of a chlorinated alkylphenone. An alkylphenone is an aromatic polyketide with methyl and chlorine substitutions.

label.value: negative regulation of positive chemotaxis to cAMP by chlorinated alkylphenone

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of directed movement of a motile cell or organism up a concentration gradient of 3',5'-cAMP by the action of a chlorinated alkylphenone. An alkylphenone is an aromatic polyketide with methyl and chlorine substitutions.

label.value: positive regulation of positive chemotaxis to cAMP by DIF-1

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of directed movement of a motile cell or organism up a concentration gradient of 3',5'-cAMP by the action of DIF-1. DIF-1 is a chlorinated alkylphenone.

label.value: negative regulation of positive chemotaxis to cAMP by DIF-1

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of directed movement of a motile cell or organism up a concentration gradient of 3',5'-cAMP by the action of DIF-1. DIF-1 is a chlorinated alkylphenone.

label.value: positive regulation of chemotaxis to cAMP by DIF-2

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of directed movement of a motile cell or organism up a concentration gradient of 3',5'-cAMP by the action of DIF-2. DIF-2 is a chlorinated alkylphenone.

label.value: negative regulation of positive chemotaxis to cAMP by DIF-2

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of directed movement of a motile cell or organism up a concentration gradient of 3',5'-cAMP by the action of DIF-2. DIF-2 is a chlorinated alkylphenone.

label.value: pancreatic bud formation

value.value: The morphogenetic process in which the foregut region specified to become the pancreas forms a bud.
